    "rationale": "Twelve of thirteen V&V 40 credibility factors meet or exceed the required level. The single shortfall (Test conditions, achieved 2 vs. required 3) is accepted because the COU is explicitly scoped to the ASTM F1717 standard test configuration and no extrapolation beyond that condition is claimed. All primary QoIs satisfy the pre-established acceptance bounds (E/uval < 1.96; percent difference < 10%). The FEA modeling framework is assessed as sufficiently credible to support the regulatory submission decision for the non-cannulated 7.5 mm pedicle screw construct.",
